entry.title: US--California Bar Shooting
entry.rights: Copyright 2018 The Associated Press. All rights reserved. This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed.
entry.summary: Thirteen people, including a sheriff's sergeant and a gunman, are dead after a shooting at a Southern California country music bar. The attack took place in Thousand Oaks, at a bar popular with students from nearby California Lutheran University. Authorities say the motive is under investigation. The killer has been identified as a 28-year-old former Marine.
entry.content: 'Horrific scene': 13 dead including gunman at California bar

entry.title: US--Election 2018-Governor-Georgia
entry.rights: Copyright 2018 The Associated Press. All rights reserved. This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed.
entry.summary: Republican Brian Kemp resigned Thursday as Georgia's secretary of state, a day after he said he'd captured enough votes to become governor. His rival has conceded nothing. As Georgia's top election official, Kemp oversaw the race. His resignation came as a hearing began for a lawsuit in which five voters asked that he be barred from exercising duties in any future management of his election tally. Democrat Stacey Abrams made concerns that he supervised the election a central issue.
entry.content: GOP gov candidate Kemp resigns as Georgia secretary of state

entry.title: US--California Bar Shooting-Victims
entry.rights: Copyright 2018 The Associated Press. All rights reserved. This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed.
entry.summary: Friends are remembering sheriff's sergeant who was killed trying to stop a shooting rampage at a California bar as a "cop's cop" who didn't hesitate to run toward danger. Ventura County sheriff's Sgt. Ron Helus died of gunshot wounds trying to stop gunman Ian David Long, who authorities say opened fire in a packed country music bar, killing 12 before police believe he turned the gun on himself. Colleagues of Helus describe him as a friend and an exceptional man and officer.

entry.title: US--California Bar Shooting-The Latest
entry.rights: Copyright 2018 The Associated Press. All rights reserved. This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed.
entry.summary: The mayor of Thousand Oaks, California, says next-of-kin notifications are being prepared about the people who were killed and injured at the mass shooting inside a bar in the city. Mayor Andrew Fox says it is going to be a "very difficult day for many people." Twelve people were shot and killed late Wednesday by the gunman who opened fire at the Borderline Bar and Grill, which was holding a weekly country music dance night for college students.

entry.title: US--Supreme Court-Ginsburg
entry.rights: Copyright 2018 The Associated Press. All rights reserved. This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed.
entry.summary: The Supreme Court says 85-year-old Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg fractured three ribs in a fall in her office at the court and is in the hospital. The court says its oldest justice fell Wednesday evening and went to George Washington University Hospital in Washington early Thursday after experiencing discomfort overnight. In Ginsburg's absence, the court is going ahead with a ceremony welcoming new Justice Brett Kavanaugh, who joined the court last month.
entry.content: Ginsburg, 85, hospitalized after fracturing 3 ribs in fall

entry.title: US-Missouri-Boat-Accident
entry.rights: Copyright 2018 The Associated Press. All rights reserved. This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed.
entry.summary: Charges have been filed against the captain of a Missouri tourist boat that sank and killed 17 people, including nine from an Indiana family. A federal indictment released Thursday charges 51-year-old Kenneth Scott McKee with 17 counts of misconduct, negligence or inattention to duty by a ship's officer resulting in death. The deaths occurred in July when an amphibious vessel known as a duck boat sank in a severe storm on a Missouri lake. The dead also included people from Arkansas and Illinois.

entry.title: US--Wired Nature
entry.rights: Copyright 2018 The Associated Press. All rights reserved. This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed.
entry.summary: Scientists have equipped a Massachusetts marshland with wireless sensors, cameras and microphones to create a virtual reality world inspired by nature's rhythms. Researchers at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology hope that by live-streaming data, sights and sounds at the Tidmarsh Wildlife Sanctuary, they can help scientists understand wildlife restoration techniques. It will also let people experience nature remotely.

entry.title: US--El Chapo-Prosecution
entry.rights: Copyright 2018 The Associated Press. All rights reserved. This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed.
entry.summary: A jury has been picked for the U.S. trial of the Mexican drug lord known as El Chapo. Seven women and five men were selected Wednesday as jurors in the case against Joaquin Guzman. The trial is set to begin Nov. 13 with opening statements in federal court in Brooklyn. Guzman has pleaded not guilty to charges, including overseeing a violent drug cartel known for violence and escaping Mexican jails twice.

entry.title: US--Shooting-Two Killed
entry.rights: Copyright 2018 The Associated Press. All rights reserved. This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed.
entry.summary: Authorities say two Texas law enforcement officers and one of their wives are at the center of an investigation into a double homicide that rattled the upstate New York town of Sodus. A neighbor had told police that Joshua Niles and Amber Washburn were fatally shot outside their home Oct. 20 with their 4-year-old son nearby. The wife of the Texas officer accused of murdering the couple is the ex-girlfriend of the male victim, and mother of two of his other children.
entry.content: Texas police charged in double homicide in stricken NY town

entry.title: US--Anti-Abortion Activist Released
entry.rights: Copyright 2018 The Associated Press. All rights reserved. This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed.
entry.summary: An anti-abortion activist who shot and wounded Kansas abortion doctor George Tiller in 1993 and committed clinic attacks in several states has been released from prison in Oregon. The U.S. Bureau of Prisons on Wednesday confirmed the release of 62-year-old Rachelle "Shelley" Shannon. She was sentenced to 20 years for fire bombings and acid attacks at abortion clinics in California, Oregon and Nevada. She received 11 years for shooting Tiller, who was killed in 2009 by an anti-abortion extremist.
entry.content: Anti-abortion activist who shot Kansas abortion doctor freed
